'''Toba Shrine''' (とばじんじゃ) is a shrine enshrined in {{ill|lt=Nagahama|Q844130|WD=Q844130|1=Nagahama, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}. Its {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=former shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|WD=Q712534}} was {{ill|lt=Sonsha|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
It has {{ill|lt=Tori no Iwakusunofune no Kami|Q10731425|WD=Q10731425|lt=Toriiwa Kusunokifune-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-torifune}} as its principal deity, with {{ill|lt=Emperor Chūai|Q179971|WD=Q179971|1=Emperor Chūai}} and {{ill|lt=Empress Jingū|Q232803|WD=Q232803|1=Empress Jingū}} as associated deities.

=== History ===
Tradition says it was founded in {{ill|lt=684|Q31128|WD=Q31128|1=684}} (Hakuhō 13). It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Engishiki shrine|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286|lt=Shikinaisha}}. In October {{ill|lt=1876|Q7766|WD=Q7766|1=1876}} (Meiji 9), it was ranked as a {{ill|lt=Sonsha|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}, and in {{ill|lt=1909|Q2057|WD=Q2057|1=1909}} (Meiji 42) it was designated as a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shinsen Heihaku-ryō Kyōshinsha|1=UNKNOWN}}.

